<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Divide
 your CAPI questionnaire into sections, one for each topic area. Add any
 special sections, such a begin and end section or global help sections,
 like an FAQ. These sections organizing units for defining forms and movement
 within the application.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Break
 up the questions within a section into forms containing one or several
 responses. Remember, you only have about Â½ of the screen at the bottom
 to use for a form, because the question text may take up the top half
 of the screen.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">If
 the form contains a roster, you should make sure that only the roster
 scrolls, not the form. Scrolling forms are confusing to interviewers.</font></p>
